n: Hard Boiled Eggs in the Oven
des: "This is an easy alternative to boiling when you need to make a lot of eggs at once. Red dots may appear on the shells and a little on the whites, but you can cut away those parts. The eggs still taste great."
ins:
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
Put 1 egg in each of 12 muffin cups.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Plunge baked eggs in a large bowl filled with ice water until cooled completely, about 10 minutes.
